  <span id="freeText15734023309272887685" style="display:none">While in today’s social milieu, Siddhartha packing bags and escaping would be the common scenario. Happens all the time, least of which for finding enlightenment. It is however plausible that Gopa/ Yashodhara was extraordinary in showing understanding and love. That too exists *today* if one is fortunate to encounter it. Plus, the fact that Gautama was already compassionate towards life from his younger day encounters with hunting, he probably did not just walk out. Whether the husband and wife discussed or not, he probably felt compelled to find solitude to seek the way while ensuring his family was cared for before he left.<br />This is not exactly like immaculate conception :) The scenario is fairy human.</span>
